---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { site } from "../data/site";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy" description="Privacy overview for Support Youth DJs public-link directory submissions, moderation, administrative contact data, correction, and removal.">
  <section class="page-head">
    <div class="page-head-inner">
      <p class="stamp">Privacy</p>
      <h1>Privacy Overview</h1>
      <p class="lead">Support Youth DJs collects only the information needed to review public-link directory submissions, respond to messages, maintain resources, and operate the platform responsibly.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <p class="kicker">Draft privacy language for legal review.</p>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="panel"><h2>Directory Intake</h2><p>Directory intake may ask for public DJ name, age range, city, state, genres, submitter role, public URLs, administrative contact email, and review acknowledgements.</p></article>
        <article class="panel"><h2>Public Links</h2><p>Phase 1 submissions are links-only. Support Youth DJs does not accept uploads through the directory intake. Public external links may lead to platforms outside Support Youth DJs.</p></article>
        <article class="panel"><h2>Age Routing</h2><p>DJs ages 13-17 may initiate their own directory submission. DJs under 13 require parent or legal guardian submission. Adults are not eligible for directory profiles.</p></article>
        <article class="panel"><h2>Staff-Entered Details</h2><p>Brief profile text, categories, related resources, or editorial context may be entered internally by staff during review before publication.</p></article>
        <article class="panel"><h2>Administrative Contact</h2><p>Emails sent to {site.contactEmail} or {site.shopEmail} may be used to answer directory, parent, profile correction, profile removal, editorial, resource, contributor, or merchandise questions.</p></article>
        <article class="panel"><h2>Merchandise and Affiliate Links</h2><p>If merchandise or affiliate links are used, outside providers may process payments, shipping, analytics, click tracking, or purchases according to their own policies.</p></article>
      </div>
      <ul class="list"><li>Private phone numbers, private emails, home addresses, schools, exact birth dates, private schedules, and sensitive family information should not be submitted for publication.</li><li>Every directory submission is reviewed before publication. There is no automatic publication.</li><li>Parents, guardians, youth DJs, or appropriate contacts may request correction or removal of a published profile or public link.</li><li>This overview is not final legal advice and should be reviewed before large-scale submissions, paid advertising, or expanded data collection begin.</li></ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
